\b Kerry Internal Technical Update: Azure + Terraform MCP Implementation\b0\par
\par
\b Objective\b0\par
Build and validate a repeatable MCP-based workflow for cloud operations that supports discovery, governance checks, and controlled remediation.\par
\par
\b Architecture implemented\b0\par
- Azure MCP container for Azure-side operations\par
- Terraform MCP container for Terraform Cloud or Enterprise operations\par
- Local operator context using Azure CLI authentication and scoped environment selection\par
- Documentation updates to support repeatable setup and run patterns\par
\par
\b Core workflow\b0\par
1. Authenticate and select target cloud scope\par
2. Start MCP services and verify runtime status\par
3. Run discovery and posture queries\par
4. Review findings and identify remediation candidates\par
5. Execute cleanup only after explicit approval\par
6. Perform post-change validation checks\par
\par
\b Technical capabilities now available\b0\par
- Resource group and resource inventory summaries\par
- Public IP and network hygiene analysis\par
- Tag compliance checks against required metadata\par
- VM and bastion state visibility\par
- Drift-oriented comparison between live cloud resources and Terraform state\par
\par
\b Safety model and guardrails\b0\par
- Read-first operational posture by default\par
- Human approval gate for destructive operations\par
- Verification pass after each change to confirm expected state\par
- Security guidance to keep credentials and tokens out of source control\par
\par
\b Implementation notes\b0\par
- Use environment variables for runtime secrets and tokens\par
- Keep local-only values in ignored files\par
- Keep setup docs generic for reuse across teams and environments\par
- Prefer small, auditable change sets with explicit rollback paths\par
\par
\b Recommended next steps\b0\par
1. Package common query sets into reusable runbooks\par
2. Add automated governance snapshots on a fixed cadence\par
3. Define escalation and ownership mapping for remediation findings\par
4. Expand to additional environments after pilot validation\par
\par
\b Operational handoff\b0\par
The current setup is ready for team onboarding sessions and incremental adoption in production-adjacent environments with existing approval controls.\par
